27/10/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The court of BiH accepted on Tuesday (October 26th) a plea bargain between prosecutors and Bosnian Serb Dragan Rodic, sentencing him to eight years in prison for war crimes and crimes against humanity committed against Bosniak and Croatian prisoners of war during the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict. 
Rodic was convicted of helping to establish and maintain a punishment and abuse system in the Slavko Rodic school building and the Kamenica detention camp in the Drvar area, where prisoners of war were tortured and killed. 
(RTRS, Srna - 26/10/10)
